label: Tax Free Records
description:
If The Durutti Column made a record at the Radiophonic Workshop it’d prob sound a bit like this; percolated electronic treatments bubbling around pure guitar drift, a beautiful thing.

IRIS are named after a Soviet-era Czech guitar: the Jolana Iris. On the opening track 'Rub Ix', arhythmic synth tones remind of Raymond Scott's pioneering experimentation, but the light shimmer of guitar strings tickles in the background.
